
[1]sobriety

   SOBRI'ETY, n. [L. sobrietas, from sobrius.]

   1. Habitual soberness or temperance in the use of spirituous liquors;
   as when we say. a man of sobriety.

   2. Freedom from intoxication. Public sobriety is a relative duty.

   3. Habitual freedom from enthusiasm, inordinate passion or overheated
   imagination; calmness; coolness; as the sobriety of riper years; the
   sobriety of age.

   4. Seriousness; gravity without sadness or melancholy. Mirth makes them
   not mad, nor sobriety sad.
